  "text": "PKs and their receptors are expressed in the testis and the prostate. In the testis, PK1 is predominantly expressed in testosterone-producing Leydig cells, whereas PK2 is restricted to primary spermatocytes [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The PKRs are expressed in vascular endothelial cells in the testis [CITATION_3] . Interestingly, in the mouse testis, PKR1 and PKR2 are expressed equally, whereas in the human testis, PKR1 is expressed at higher levels in comparison to PKR2 [CITATION_4] . The exact role of each of these receptors and the implications of differential levels of expression remain to be elucidated.",
